# Shade Chasers — Foundation

## Game Concept

A multiplayer 3D race-to-shelter game. Players sprint through a post-apocalyptic landscape where the sun is lethal radiation. Shadows cast by obstacles are the only safe zones. The sun moves over time, so shadows shift — players must read the environment and adapt their path in real time.

## Core Loop

1. Players join a web lobby, get a random (changeable) username
2. Up to 20 players per lobby; game starts after 60 s countdown or when full
3. All players start simultaneously and race on foot toward a finish-line shelter
4. Exposure to sunlight drains a tolerance meter; depletion = death
5. Collectible items (e.g. protective clothing) scattered on the map extend tolerance
6. Shadows move with the sun — safe routes change over time

## Visual Identity

- Stylized cartoon 3D, medium-low poly, flat shading with sharp edges
- Desaturated / overexposed look in sunlit areas (color burned away)
- Deep blacks, indigos, violets, blues with high saturation in shadowed areas
- Simple chunky obstacles, minimal texture detail
- High contrast between sun and shadow zones is the defining visual trait

## Controls

- WASD movement, mouse camera (third-person, Fall Guys-style feel)

## Tech Stack

React, Three.js, React Three Fiber, @react-three/drei, @react-three/rapier, TypeScript, Vite. Additional libraries will be introduced as needed — do not add dependencies preemptively.

