## Development Methodology

### Incremental Approach

Do NOT implement multiple features at once. Each piece of functionality must be working and verifiable before building the next thing on top of it. When a feature is complete, confirm it works before moving on.

### Planning Requirement

Before implementing any sufficiently large feature, create an implementation plan as a markdown file and present it for review before execution. A "sufficiently large feature" = anything that touches 3+ files or introduces a new system.

### Clarification Obligation

Ask about any vague, ambiguous, or conflicting detail before writing code. Do not assume intent — confirm it.

### No Premature Abstraction

Do not create elaborate folder structures, abstractions, or systems ahead of the concrete need. Let architecture emerge from actual requirements. Build the simplest thing that works, then refactor when complexity demands it.
